alists could attest-but that the aims and self-understanding of the two \\\"revolutions\\\" were fundamentally at odds.\", \"from\": 3806, \"to\": 3987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3834, \"end\": 3851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriot_(American_Revolution)\", \"score\": 0.9999993611365647, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American patriots\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriot_(American_Revolution)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriot_(American_Revolution)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"angels\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3863}, {\"ngram\": \"the loyalists\", \"from\": 3867, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"the aims\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3911}, {\"ngram\": \"self-understanding\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 3934}, {\"ngram\": \"the two \\\"revolutions\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3958}, {\"ngram\": \"odds\", \"from\": 3982, \"to\": 3986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nowhere are the differences more glaring than when it comes to religious liberty.\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 4069, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the differences\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4015}, {\"ngram\": \"religious liberty\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By and large, the American founding fathers-whatever their eclectic personal beliefs-saw religion as \\\"a necessary spring of popular government,\\\" as George Washington put it in his farewell address.\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4088, \"end\": 4096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4218, \"end\": 4235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.590673919595659e-26, \"text\": \"George Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 4114, \"to\": 4122}, {\"ngram\": \"their eclectic personal beliefs-saw religion\", \"from\": 4123, \"to\": 4167}, {\"ngram\": \"a necessary spring\", \"from\": 4172, \"to\": 4190}, {\"ngram\": \"popular government\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4212}, {\"ngram\": \"his farewell address\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American religious minorities, including Baptists and Catholics, supported the First Amendment precisely because they understood it to protect, not limit, the practice and expression of religion.\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4268, \"end\": 4276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4309, \"end\": 4317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baptists\", \"score\": 0.9999994253668606, \"rank\": 5.604771057129847e-07, \"text\": \"Baptists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baptists\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baptists\"}, {\"begin\": 4322, \"end\": 4331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999997773620882, \"rank\": 2.2263822515540546e-07, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the First Amendment\", \"from\": 4343, \"to\": 4362}, {\"ngram\": \"religion\", \"from\": 4454, \"to\": 4462}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, by contrast, despite early support for moderate reforms among the clergy, the revolutionaries came to see Catholicism (rightly) as woven into the very fabric of French society-the society they aimed to destroy.\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4468, \"end\": 4474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 4637, \"end\": 4643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4487}, {\"ngram\": \"early support\", \"from\": 4497, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"moderate reforms\", \"from\": 4515, \"to\": 4531}, {\"ngram\": \"the clergy\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4548}, {\"ngram\": \"the revolutionaries\", \"from\": 4550, \"to\": 4569}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholicism\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4593}, {\"ngram\": \"the very fabric\", \"from\": 4618, \"to\": 4633}, {\"ngram\": \"the society\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 4663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Revolution proceeded from mob violence to organized terror, it assumed ever more grandiose-indeed, messianic-pretensions.\", \"from\": 4687, \"to\": 4815, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Revolution\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4704}, {\"ngram\": \"mob violence\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4732}, {\"ngram\": \"organized terror\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4752}, {\"ngram\": \"ever more grandiose-indeed, messianic-pretensions\", \"from\": 4765, \"to\": 4814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Alexis de Tocquevilleobserveddecades later, the revolutionaries eventually saw themselves as ushering in the \\\"regeneration of the whole human race.\\\"\", \"from\": 4816, \"to\": 4967, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alexis\", \"from\": 4819, \"to\": 4825}, {\"ngram\": \"the revolutionaries\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 4882}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"regeneration\", \"from\": 4924, \"to\": 4941}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole human race\", \"from\": 4945, \"to\": 4965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American understanding of religious liberty sees religious expression-while remaining neutral on most details-as a good.\", \"from\": 4969, \"to\": 5093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4973, \"end\": 4981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"religious liberty\", \"from\": 4999, \"to\": 5016}, {\"ngram\": \"religious expression\", \"from\": 5022, \"to\": 5042}, {\"ngram\": \"most details\", \"from\": 5070, \"to\": 5082}, {\"ngram\": \"a good\", \"from\": 5086, \"to\": 5092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is concerned to protect religious minorities from state oppression, while the French revolutionary ethos eventually offered an alternative state religion and instituted an explicit program of \\\"dechristianization.\\\"\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5175, \"end\": 5181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"religious minorities\", \"from\": 5121, \"to\": 5141}, {\"ngram\": \"state oppression\", \"from\": 5147, \"to\": 5163}, {\"ngram\": \"an alternative state religion\", \"from\": 5221, \"to\": 5250}, {\"ngram\": \"an explicit program\", \"from\": 5266, \"to\": 5285}, {\"ngram\": \"dechristianization\", \"from\": 5290, \"to\": 5308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The period that followed was among the most intense and brutal persecutions in the church's history.\", \"from\": 5312, \"to\": 5412, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The period\", \"from\": 5312, \"to\": 5322}, {\"ngram\": \"the most intense and brutal persecutions\", \"from\": 5347, \"to\": 5387}, {\"ngram\": \"the church's history\", \"from\": 5391, \"to\": 5411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Worship and the celebration of the sacraments were forbidden and tens of thousands of Catholics killed.\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5499, \"end\": 5508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999997773620882, \"rank\": 2.2263822515540546e-07, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Worship\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5420}, {\"ngram\": \"the celebration\", \"from\": 5425, \"to\": 5440}, {\"ngram\": \"the sacraments\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5458}, {\"ngram\": \"tens of thousands\", \"from\": 5478, \"to\": 5495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bloody persecution recurred during the reign of the Paris Commune, and the archbishop of Paris was executed in 1871.\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5606, \"end\": 5611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.919286567889101e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bloody persecution\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5535}, {\"ngram\": \"the reign\", \"from\": 5552, \"to\": 5561}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Commune\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5582}, {\"ngram\": \"the archbishop\", \"from\": 5588, \"to\": 5602}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Napoleon allowed Catholics to worship but made sure the church was subordinated to the state.\", \"from\": 5634, \"to\": 5727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5634, \"end\": 5642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1618605022067214e-65, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 5651, \"end\": 5660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999997773620882, \"rank\": 2.2263822515540546e-07, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the church\", \"from\": 5686, \"to\": 5696}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 5717, \"to\": 5726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French principle ofla\\u00efcit\\u00e9, in fact, gives a fancy name to low-level religious discrimination, institutionalizing bias against religious expression.\", \"from\": 5729, \"to\": 5881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5733, \"end\": 5739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 5764, \"to\": 5768}, {\"ngram\": \"a fancy name\", \"from\": 5776, \"to\": 5788}, {\"ngram\": \"low-level religious discrimination\", \"from\": 5792, \"to\": 5826}, {\"ngram\": \"bias\", \"from\": 5847, \"to\": 5851}, {\"ngram\": \"religious expression\", \"from\": 5860, \"to\": 5880}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blasphemy-such as we saw at the Olympic opening ceremony-is allowed, but public expressions of faith are intolerable.\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 5999, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Blasphemy\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 5891}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic opening ceremony\", \"from\": 5910, \"to\": 5938}, {\"ngram\": \"public expressions\", \"from\": 5955, \"to\": 5973}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 5977, \"to\": 5982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An equally ugly icon of this instinct to discriminate was the scene of four armed French police officers standing over a Muslim woman andforcing her to remove her clothingon a beach in Nice-all facilitated by an irrational antipathy to faith masquerading as constitutional principle.\", \"from\": 6000, \"to\": 6283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6082, \"end\": 6095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.785354088255307e-41, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 6121, \"end\": 6127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9911769299370687, \"rank\": 0.008901609588093435, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An equally ugly icon\", \"from\": 6000, \"to\": 6020}, {\"ngram\": \"this instinct\", \"from\": 6024, \"to\": 6037}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 6058, \"to\": 6067}, {\"ngram\": \"her clothingon\", \"from\": 6159, \"to\": 6173}, {\"ngram\": \"a beach\", \"from\": 6174, \"to\": 6181}, {\"ngram\": \"Nice-all\", \"from\": 6185, \"to\": 6193}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 6236, \"to\": 6241}, {\"ngram\": \"constitutional principle\", \"from\": 6258, \"to\": 6282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the great ironies of the French Revolution has always been the way it was forced to ape the culture it sought to replace.\", \"from\": 6285, \"to\": 6413, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the great ironies\", \"from\": 6292, \"to\": 6309}, {\"ngram\": \"the French Revolution\", \"from\": 6313, \"to\": 6334}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 6351, \"to\": 6358}, {\"ngram\": \"the culture\", \"from\": 6380, \"to\": 6391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The revolutionaries replaced the Gregorian calendar and made 1789 the new Year One.\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6497, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The revolutionaries\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6433}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gregorian calendar\", \"from\": 6443, \"to\": 6465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Revolutionary feast days (the Day of Genius!)\", \"from\": 6498, \"to\": 6543, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Revolutionary feast days\", \"from\": 6498, \"to\": 6522}, {\"ngram\": \"(the Day\", \"from\": 6523, \"to\": 6531}, {\"ngram\": \"Genius\", \"from\": 6535, \"to\": 6541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"replaced Christmas and Easter.\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6574, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christmas\", \"from\": 6553, \"to\": 6562}, {\"ngram\": \"Easter\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6573}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like adolescents in a role-playing game, the revolutionaries came up with new religions-like Theophilanthropy-to go with their new holidays.\", \"from\": 6575, \"to\": 6715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"adolescents\", \"from\": 6580, \"to\": 6591}, {\"ngram\": \"a role-playing game\", \"from\": 6595, \"to\": 6614}, {\"ngram\": \"the revolutionaries\", \"from\": 6616, \"to\": 6635}, {\"ngram\": \"new religions-like Theophilanthropy\", \"from\": 6649, \"to\": 6684}, {\"ngram\": \"their new holidays\", \"from\": 6696, \"to\": 6714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They even added a cult of relics, parading the bones of Voltaire into Paris in solemn procession to be entombed in a former church.\", \"from\": 6716, \"to\": 6847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6772, \"end\": 6780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Voltaire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0445499977024917e-54, \"text\": \"Voltaire\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Voltaire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Voltaire\"}, {\"begin\": 6786, \"end\": 6791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.919286567889101e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a cult\", \"from\": 6732, \"to\": 6738}, {\"ngram\": \"relics\", \"from\": 6742, \"to\": 6748}, {\"ngram\": \"the bones\", \"from\": 6759, \"to\": 6768}, {\"ngram\": \"solemn procession\", \"from\": 6795, \"to\": 6812}, {\"ngram\": \"a former church\", \"from\": 6831, \"to\": 6846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inventing a female figure to replace the Virgin Mary, they came up with\\u2026Marianne.\", \"from\": 6848, \"to\": 6929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6889, \"end\": 6900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999922865754, \"rank\": 7.713556110506025e-09, \"text\": \"Virgin Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 6920, \"end\": 6928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.728193324372034e-26, \"text\": \"Marianne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a female figure\", \"from\": 6858, \"to\": 6873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The revolutionaries, in other words, were forced to pirate the forms of a once-great Christian culture because they did not have enough cultural substance of their own for a truly creative endeavor.\", \"from\": 6931, \"to\": 7129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7016, \"end\": 7033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_culture\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_culture\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The revolutionaries\", \"from\": 6931, \"to\": 6950}, {\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 6955, \"to\": 6966}, {\"ngram\": \"the forms\", \"from\": 6990, \"to\": 6999}, {\"ngram\": \"enough cultural substance\", \"from\": 7060, \"to\": 7085}, {\"ngram\": \"a truly creative endeavor\", \"from\": 7103, \"to\": 7128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French, after all, have a lot to be proud of culturally-from Chartres Cathedral to Mont Saint-Michel, from Joan of Arc to Th\\u00e9r\\u00e8se of Lisieux-but without Christianity, what's left to celebrate is rather less impressive (Foucault-really?).\", \"from\": 7133, \"to\": 7374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7137, \"end\": 7143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7290, \"end\": 7302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999964384187, \"rank\": 3.5361413307920677e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 7161, \"to\": 7166}, {\"ngram\": \"Chartres Cathedral\", \"from\": 7198, \"to\": 7216}, {\"ngram\": \"Mont Saint-Michel\", \"from\": 7220, \"to\": 7237}, {\"ngram\": \"Joan\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7248}, {\"ngram\": \"Arc\", \"from\": 7252, \"to\": 7255}, {\"ngram\": \"Th\\u00e9r\\u00e8se\", \"from\": 7259, \"to\": 7266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Years ago, when visiting Paris-as beautiful as its reputation is-I remember going to the Eiffel Tower and, when I got up close, thinking, \\\"It's impressive from a distance, but up close it's just a lot of steel girders and empty space.\\\"\", \"from\": 7375, \"to\": 7610, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 7400, \"to\": 7405}, {\"ngram\": \"its reputation\", \"from\": 7422, \"to\": 7436}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 7460, \"to\": 7476}, {\"ngram\": \"a distance\", \"from\": 7535, \"to\": 7545}, {\"ngram\": \"just a lot\", \"from\": 7565, \"to\": 7575}, {\"ngram\": \"steel girders\", \"from\": 7579, \"to\": 7592}, {\"ngram\": \"empty space\", \"from\": 7597, \"to\": 7608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What the organizers of the Paris Olympics put on display was their empty space-the vacuousness of the secular cultural project.\", \"from\": 7611, \"to\": 7738, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 7616, \"to\": 7630}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 7634, \"to\": 7652}, {\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 7660, \"to\": 7667}, {\"ngram\": \"their empty space\", \"from\": 7672, \"to\": 7689}, {\"ngram\": \"the vacuousness\", \"from\": 7690, \"to\": 7705}, {\"ngram\": \"the secular cultural project\", \"from\": 7709, \"to\": 7737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, that vacuousness is what makes the mockery of Christianity at the Paris Olympics so dull.\", \"from\": 7740, \"to\": 7841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7798, \"end\": 7810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999964384187, \"rank\": 3.5361413307920677e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 7743, \"to\": 7750}, {\"ngram\": \"that vacuousness\", \"from\": 7752, \"to\": 7768}, {\"ngram\": \"the mockery\", \"from\": 7783, \"to\": 7794}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 7814, \"to\": 7832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even with all the resources at their disposal-mounds of corporate funds and French tax euros-all they could do was cannibalize Christian forms.\", \"from\": 7842, \"to\": 7985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7918, \"end\": 7924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7969, \"end\": 7984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian forms\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the resources\", \"from\": 7852, \"to\": 7869}, {\"ngram\": \"their disposal-mounds\", \"from\": 7873, \"to\": 7894}, {\"ngram\": \"corporate funds\", \"from\": 7898, \"to\": 7913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France did not put its best foot forward at the opening ceremony, and I am especially sorry for my French Catholic friends.\", \"from\": 7987, \"to\": 8110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7987, \"end\": 7993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 8086, \"end\": 8092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 8093, \"end\": 8101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3061748155741023e-17, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its best foot\", \"from\": 8006, \"to\": 8019}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 8031, \"to\": 8051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's particularly nasty to beat up on a cultural minority at an event like the Olympics, and France's bishops are right to protest.\", \"from\": 8111, \"to\": 8242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8204, \"end\": 8210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a cultural minority\", \"from\": 8149, \"to\": 8168}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 8172, \"to\": 8180}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 8186, \"to\": 8198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But whatever happens, I suspect I will probably doze through the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 8243, \"to\": 8325, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 8247, \"to\": 8255}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 8304, \"to\": 8324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe they will use a guillotine to snuff out the Olympic flame.\", \"from\": 8326, \"to\": 8390, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a guillotine\", \"from\": 8346, \"to\": 8358}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flame\", \"from\": 8372, \"to\": 8389}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anthony R. Lusvardi, S.J., teaches sacramental theology at the Pontifical Gregorian Universit